{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かちん}}

First attested in {{w|Muromachi period}} texts.

Originally a {{m|ja|女房詞|tr={{w|nyōbō kotoba}}|lit=woman's language}} term, derived as a compound of {{m|ja||搗ち|tr=kachi}}, the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||stem or continuative form}} of verb {{m|ja|搗つ|tr=katsu||to [[pound]] in a [[mortar]]}} + {{m|ja|飯|tr=ii||[[cook]]ed [[grain]]s}}.<ref name="KDJ"/><ref name="DJS"/><ref name="DJR"/> The final {{m|ja|ん|tr=-n}} is likely an informal suffix.  Listed as ''cachin'' in the ''{{w|Nippo Jisho}}'' of 1603.<ref>{{R:Nippo Jisho original}}, text [https://books.google.com/books?id=TFJAAQAAMAAJ&dq=%22%E6%97%A5%E8%91%A1%E8%BE%9E%E6%9B%B8%22&pg=PP71#v=onepage&q=%22%E6%97%A5%E8%91%A1%E8%BE%9E%E6%9B%B8%22&f=false here] as the fifth entry from the bottom of the right-hand column</ref>

{{ja-noun|kyu=餠|かちん}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=かちん|colloquial}} [[mochi]] {{gloss|Japanese [[rice cake]] made from [[glutinous rice]], usually [[mix]]ed with other [[ingredient]]s}}
#: {{synonyms|ja|おかちん|tr=o-kachin}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|あも}}

{{IPAchar|/amːot͡ɕi/}} → {{IPAchar|/amːo/}} → {{IPAchar|/amo/}}

A shift from {{m|ja|餡餅||tr=anmochi|[[red bean]]-[[paste]] [[mochi]]}}, deriving from [[baby talk]].<ref name="KDJ"/><ref name="DJS"/><ref name="DJR"/>  Appears in the ''{{w|Nippo Jisho}}'' of 1603, described as {{m|pt|“[[palavra|Palaura]] [[de]] [[mulheres]], [[e|🙰]] [[meninos|mininos]]”||a women's and children's word}}.<ref>{{R:Nippo Jisho original}}, text [https://books.google.com/books?id=TFJAAQAAMAAJ&dq=%22%E6%97%A5%E8%91%A1%E8%BE%9E%E6%9B%B8%22&pg=PP28#v=onepage&q=%22%E6%97%A5%E8%91%A1%E8%BE%9E%E6%9B%B8%22&f=false here], third entry from the bottom in the right-hand column</ref>

{{ja-noun|kyu=餠|あも}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=あも|usually|_|childish}} [[mochi]] [[fill]]ed or [[wrap]]ped in [[red bean]] [[paste]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|餡餅|tr=anmochi, anmo}}
# {{lb|ja|sort=あも|usually|_|childish|by extension}} [[mochi]] {{gloss|Japanese [[rice cake]] made from [[glutinous rice]], usually [[mix]]ed with other [[ingredient]]s}}
